# Charity Donation Platform

## Description
This is a code for a charity donation platform, which shows information about charity organisations, donors, and their donations.


## Entities

### Donor
Represents a person who makes a donation

### Charity
Represents a charity organization

### Donation
Represents a donation made by a donor to a charity

### DonationPool
Stores and manages all donations
Functions:
- Add donations
- Print all donations
- Filter donations by charity
- Search donations by donor
- Sort donations by amount


##  Instruction

Input charity organisation names, donor names, amount and types of donations in main.java file. Program will automatically input them and then sort them.

## Assignment task fulfilled:
-this is a continuation of a project
-follows data abstraction principle

"public abstract class Entity {
    private final int id;
    private String name;
}"

-it sortrs output with a data pool, filtering, searching and sorting

"DonationPool pool = new DonationPool();
pool.filterByCharity("WWF")
pool.searchByDonor("Anatoliy Pirozhkov")
pool.sortByAmount()"

-encapsulation, inheritance and polymorphism implemented

"private String name;
private int id;"

"public String getName()
public void setName(String name)"

"public class Donor extends Entity
public class Charity extends Entity"

"System.out.println(entity);"

-override toString (), equals (), hashCode () methods are used


@Override
public String toString() {
    return getClass().getSimpleName() + "{" +
            "id=" + id +
            ", name='" + name + '\'' +
            '}';
}


@Override
public boolean equals(Object o)


@Override
public int hashCode() {
    return Objects.hash(id, name);
}
